#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Kulāvakasutta "
msgstr "6. Bird Nests "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn11.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.6:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "sn11.6:1.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme asurā jiniṃsu, devā parājiniṃsu. "
msgstr "In that battle the demons won and the gods lost. "

msgctxt "sn11.6:1.4"
msgid "Parājitā ca kho, bhikkhave, devā apāyaṃsveva uttarenamukhā, abhiyaṃsveva ne asurā. "
msgstr "Defeated, the gods fled north with the demons in pursuit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.6:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātali saṅgāhakaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.484, sc2
msgctxt "sn11.6:2.1"
msgid "‘Kulāvakā mātali simbalismiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Mātali, don’t ram the bird nests "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.6:2.2"
msgid "Īsāmukhena parivajjayassu; "
msgstr "in the red silk-cotton woods with your chariot pole. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.6:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaṃ cajāma asuresu pāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "I’d rather give up our lives to the demons "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vikulāvakā → vikulāvā (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn11.6:2.4"
msgid "Māyime dijā vikulāvakā ahesun’ti. "
msgstr "than deprive these birds of their nests.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.225, sc3
msgctxt "sn11.6:3.1"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ paccudāvattesi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. And he turned the chariot back around, with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.6:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, asurānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the demons thought, "

msgctxt "sn11.6:3.3"
msgid "‘paccudāvatto kho dāni sakkassa devānamindassa sahassayutto ājaññaratho. "
msgstr "‘Now Sakka’s chariot has turned back. "

msgctxt "sn11.6:3.4"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho devā asurehi saṅgāmessantī’ti bhītā asurapurameva pāvisiṃsu. "
msgstr "The demons will have to fight the gods a second time!’ Terrified, they retreated right away to the castle of the demons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.6:3.5"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, sakkassa devānamindassa dhammena jayo ahosī”ti. "
msgstr "And that’s how Sakka came to win victory by principle.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
